Force OverlayProcessorOzone::ShouldCreatePrimaryPlane to true on
cast_shell.

The IS_CASTOS guard in upstream chromium 147 returns false from
ShouldCreatePrimaryPlane, on the assumption that Chromecast TV / Nest
Hub style hardware owns its own primary plane through a hardware video
plane the cast media pipeline drives. On bridgething the cast_shell
renderer is the only producer of output, weston is the compositor, and
there is no separate hardware primary plane.

Returning false means the root render pass is never promoted to a
primary plane OverlayCandidate in OverlayProcessorUsingStrategy::
ProcessForOverlays. The candidate list stays empty, SkiaOutputSurface
ImplOnGpu::PresentFrame skips ScheduleOverlays, and SkiaOutput
DeviceBufferQueue::Present commits the backbuffer through
presenter_->Present without any ScheduleOverlayPlane call ever
running. GbmPixmapWayland::CreateDmabufBasedWlBuffer therefore never
fires, the WaylandBufferManagerHost has no buffer backings registered
for any buffer_id, and the CommitOverlays mojo call that does reach
the host carries an empty config list. WaylandFrameManager records
an empty frame, never plays it back, and the wl_surface gets exactly
one ack_configure with no wl_buffer.attach ever following.

Patches 0006 (set_fullscreen instead of set_maximized), 0007 (opaque
black compositor backstop instead of cast's SK_ColorTRANSPARENT), and
0008 (drop kDisableGpuEarlyInit so the GPU channel comes up at
startup) were all real bugs that needed fixing, but the actual cause
of the GPU compositing wedge on this device was this primary plane
gate.

Force-returning true makes OverlayProcessorOzone behave like the
non-CastOS path: the root render pass becomes a primary plane,
InsertPrimaryPlane adds it to the candidate list, ScheduleOverlays
fires, GbmPixmapWayland creates the wl_buffer via CreateDmabufBased
WlBuffer, QueueWaylandOverlayConfig populates the GbmSurfacelessWay
land PendingFrame, MaybeSubmitFrames sends a CommitOverlays with a
real config, and the WaylandFrameManager attaches and commits the
buffer to the wl_surface. The whole chain unwedges.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

diff --git a/components/viz/service/display/overlay_processor_ozone.cc b/components/viz/service/display/overlay_processor_ozone.cc
--- a/components/viz/service/display/overlay_processor_ozone.cc
+++ b/components/viz/service/display/overlay_processor_ozone.cc
@@ -499,11 +499,16 @@
 }
 
 bool OverlayProcessorOzone::ShouldCreatePrimaryPlane() const {
-#if BUILDFLAG(IS_CASTOS)
-  return false;
-#else
+  // Upstream returns false on IS_CASTOS because Chromecast TV / Nest Hub
+  // hardware provides its own primary plane through a video plane the cast
+  // media pipeline owns. On bridgething there is no such hardware: the
+  // cast_shell renderer is the only producer of output, so the root render
+  // pass must be promoted to a primary plane overlay or no buffer ever
+  // reaches GbmSurfacelessWayland / WaylandBufferManagerHost. Without this
+  // override, the wayland xdg_toplevel acks the first configure but never
+  // sees wl_buffer.attach because the entire ScheduleOverlayPlane chain is
+  // dead on this build.
   return true;
-#endif
 }
 
